<item>
            <title>[LU-12623] sanity test 56xb fails with &apos;cannot create hard links&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12623</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity test_56xb fails with the following seen in the client test_log&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity test 56xb: lfs migration hard link support ================================================= 08:31:41 (1563438701)
striped dir -i0 -c2 /mnt/lustre/d56xb.sanity
testing lfs migrate mode when all links fit within xattrs
creating initial file...done
creating symlinks...done
creating nonlinked files...done
creating hard links 2:100... sanity test_56xb: @@@@@@ FAIL: cannot create hard links 
  Trace dump:
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6070:error()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity.sh:6279:check_migrate_links()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity.sh:6340:test_56xb()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like this test is only failing for DNE with ZFS. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is not a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10716&quot; title=&quot;interop: sanity test_56xb: FAIL: cannot create hard links&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10716&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10716&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; because none of these failures are seen in interop testing. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We&#8217;ve seen this error once in November 2018 and January 2019 during patch testing , &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b86533f0-f290-11e8-815b-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b86533f0-f290-11e8-815b-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/31cc8010-1256-11e9-b7d4-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/31cc8010-1256-11e9-b7d4-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt; respectively. The first time we saw this error in non-patch testing was in February 2019 at &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/7fb23e64-272d-11e9-a318-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/7fb23e64-272d-11e9-a318-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;. We&#8217;ve seen sanity test 56xb fail with this error 11 times since February 1, 2019 with the latest failure at&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/26145964-a973-11e9-8fc1-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/26145964-a973-11e9-8fc1-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
